    • grow

      @CheckReturnValue @Contract(pure=true) public Rectangle grow(int x, int y)
      Changes the dimensions of this Rectangle. The changes are applied symmetrically. So a change of 1 in the x-axis, means that the length of the x-axis is increased by 2 (1 subtracted from min and 1 added to max).
      Parameters:
      x - The number of blocks to change in the x-axis.
      y - The number of blocks to change in the y-axis.
      Returns:
      A new Rectangle.
